      "side": 1,
      "message": "`remove_parents_below` is a parameter that complements the `remove_empty_parents` parameter. If you want the parent to be recursively removed if they become empty after a deletion, you must define the folder from which deletion stops with `remove_parents_below`, whereas `remove_empty_parents` will only remove the parent file and nothing more.\nFor example : `/mnt/lustre/test/test2/test3/file.txt`\n\nIf the policy deletes file.txt, then with `remove_empty_parents` only `test3` is deleted. However, if you want to delete `test2` but keep `test`, you can set `remove_parents_below` on `/mnt/lustre/test/`",
